    "steps": [
      "Preheat the oven to 375°F. Halve or quarter the tomatoes and arrange on a baking sheet with the onions, garlic, and oregano. ",
      "Drizzle with olive oil, sprinkle with salt and pepper, and roast for 45 minutes, basting occasionally.",
      "Cool the roasted vegetables slightly, peel the tomato skins if desired, and transfer the vegetables and juices to a large pot. ",
      "Add chicken stock, sugar, red pepper flakes, vinegar, and basil. Simmer for 10 minutes.",
      "Purée the soup using an immersion blender until smooth. Adjust seasoning as needed.",
      "Meanwhile, fry the diced bacon until crispy and set aside. Make the croutons by tossing the bread cubes with olive oil and toasting in the oven until golden.",
      "Prepare the garlic mayonnaise by mashing two of the roasted garlic cloves and mixing with the mayonnaise.",
      "Serve the soup with bacon bits, croutons, arugula, and a drizzle of garlic mayonnaise.",
